The paper discusses a new interface for optimizing data movement across different data-intensive libraries and frameworks. This involves optimizing across disjoint libraries and functions, which suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of databases (cs.DB), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), programming languages (cs.PL), machine learning (cs.LG), and software engineering (cs.SE).
